      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAXON KELTON (1) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at Healesville in a handy 19.48 beating Tropic Man. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Can measure up again. TOP KADE (8) turned in a fair run last time from the squeeze finishing fourth by 4.5 lengths (20.14). Has a strong winning record here at this journey. Must be included in calculations. CRUISIN' GRAE (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when eighth at Warrnambool over 390m behind Bush Mayhem (22.87) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. The form out of last race has been strong. Great chance to atone. AMRON SAMMY (7) scored in dominant fashion last time. Big chance on that form.",
